Trivia.
The name Katoomba is used as a name for a on the planet Mars, though not specifically commemorating the town.
In 2001, Katoomba Returned Services League Club was the subject of an important tort case. The plaintiff was a problem gambler and alleged that the RSL Club, knowing about his addiction, owed him a duty of care to prevent him from using the gambling facilities on site. He sought to recover for the loss of the money he had gambled at the club. Whilst the plaintiff's action failed in court in a unanimous judgment, Justice Spigelman acknowledged that a duty of care may be owed toward problem gamblers in "exceptional cases".

