Honours.
Parma has won eight major titles in its history (as well as one Serie B title), all coming in a period of ten years between 1992 and 2002. These honours make it the eleventh most successful team in Italian football history in terms of the number of major trophies won, the fourth most successful team in European competition, after A.C. Milan, Juventus and Inter Milan, and one of thirteen Italian clubs to have won multiple major titles.

